Title: Superspace Representations of SU(2,2/N) Superalgebras and Multiplet
  Shortening
Authors: S. Ferrara (CERN, TH Division)
Comments: Talk given at the TMR Conference on Quantum Aspects of Gauge
  Theories, Supersymmetry and Unification, Paris, 1-7 September 1999
\\
  We derive massless and massive representations of all SU(2,2/N) superalgebras
by using superfields defined in "harmonic superspace". This method allows one
to easily construct "short superfields" which are relevant in the analysis of
the AdS/CFT correspondence.
